title: For Sale/Trade:  Hard To Find Ruger SR22RDS Rifle, New In Box, TRADE
postcontent:
You will not likely see another one of these in any gun store. Must have for the 10/22 collector, get this one while you can. These are the best tactical style .22 cal rifles made. Standard 10/22 receiver and internals inside a high quality Nordic Components aluminum chassis, with factory heavy barrel and free float handguard, all built this way factory right from Ruger. MSRP is $649 on this unique and hard to find model. You get the famous 10/22 reliability, plus all standard 10/22 mags (like the BX25) and other internal upgrades are totally compatible, since it has standard 10/22 internals. It is a very accurate package with the factory free floated heavier barrel. It is actually a .750 barrel to look and be exactly the same size as a standard AR15 barrel - a perfect compromise which is larger and more accurate than the regular 10/22 barrel, just as accurate (but still lighter) than a full HBAR (.920). I believe this is actually the only model from Ruger ever made with this "intermediate" sized barrel that mimics the specific size of the AR15/M16 barrel. It also has rails incorporated into the aluminum chassis and true free float tube, and even comes with the new Ruger brand flip up front and rear sights as well. I am including a link to this model on Ruger's website for info on specs and features. This is the model with the adjustable stock and threaded barrel with flash hider, not the "ban-states" model without those evil features. Brand new in the box complete with everything it came with, bought new by me, and never been fired once. I hate to let this rifle go, but I will for the right offer. Mainly looking for the highest end handgun I can get for it, or a new Mossberg 930SPX. But I will also consider any of the trades that are listed below, or any other cool/interesting trades that you may have. I prefer something brand new since mine is brand new, but for the right trade that is not a deal breaker. title: For Sale:  RARE WWI German V.C. Schilling and Suhl and 2 WWII German Dress Bayonets 1 Stag
postcontent:
These are from an estate and were in a safe for over 60 years. They could use cleaned. I will try to describe these to the best of my ability. In the first Picture is this very rare antique World War I German Model 1898 VC SCHILLING SUHL bayonet. The wooden handle has nice dark brown patina. The blade is marked "VC SCHILLING SUHL" Its in decent condition considering its age. I put this bayonet in a cloth sheath just to protect it The WW2 Stag dress bayonet was manufactured by WKC. Which was a well renown company for the production of high quality edge weapons during the Nazi reign. The manufacturer's logo is placed at the base of the blade. In this case is the head of a knight armor. It is important to note that not all of the blades were marked by the manufacturer. Last is the WW2 The long style blade has a wide fuller design and the nickel plating is still bright throughout with some mild age in the surfaces but the blade still grades in great condition. The obverse ricasso is stamped with the knighthead logo having the firmâs initials beneath, âW.K.&C.â. The black checkered grip plates of this bayonet are in perfect condition and are retained by steel rivets having dressed heads on the obverse. The scabbard is straight throughout having fairly good original paint. There is some age in the lower obverse areas of the paint and there are also carrying signs throughout. I accept paypal only and will ship usps as soon as payment is made. Please feel free to make me an offer. If you need any further pics please ask.
